      "FacilityID": 1000057343,
      "SummaryText": "The HWFP stores and uses chlorine as disinfection in amounts that exceed the EPA's 40 CFR part 68 threshold limit of 2,500 pounds.  The plant does not store or use any other chemicals in excess of the limits set in the standard mentioned above.  The HWFP is covered by OSHA PSM.  All applicable OSHA documents are stored at the plant, these include confined space entry, lockout/tagout, emergency evacuation, and PPE programs and procedures.  \n\n\n\nThe Hammond Water Filtration Plant (HWFP) has an emergency response plan on file with the Lake County Emergency Planning Committee.  A copy of the response plan is at the plant, accessible to all employees.  The Fire Department has recently toured the water plant to familiarize themselves with the emergency procedures.\n\n"
